Achievements & Success Stories

Celebrating the remarkable accomplishments of our distinguished alumni

Pride of JGEC

Our alumni have made significant contributions across industries, from technology and healthcare to manufacturing and entrepreneurship. Their achievements reflect the excellent education and values instilled at Jalpaiguri Government Engineering College. Here are some of their inspiring stories.

Rajesh Kumar

CEO & Founder

Rajesh Kumar

CEO & Founder, Tech Innovations Pvt Ltd

Batch of 1995Computer Science

Rajesh founded Tech Innovations in 2005 and has grown it into a multinational company with over 5000 employees. His journey from a small-town boy to a tech mogul is an inspiration to many.

Key Achievements:

  • Forbes 40 Under 40 (2015)
  • Entrepreneur of the Year - CII (2018)
  • Patent holder - 15+ technology patents

JGEC taught me that with determination and hard work, any dream is achievable. The foundation laid here has been instrumental in my success.

Dr. Priya Sharma

Director

Dr. Priya Sharma

Director, Engineering Research Institute

Batch of 2002Electrical Engineering

Dr. Priya is a renowned researcher in renewable energy systems. She has published over 50 research papers and holds 8 patents in solar energy technology.

Key Achievements:

  • National Science Award (2020)
  • Women in STEM Leadership Award (2019)
  • UNESCO Recognition for Clean Energy Research

The rigorous academic environment at JGEC prepared me for the challenges of research. I'm proud to be an alumna.

Amit Patel

Founder & CTO

Amit Patel

Founder & CTO, StartupHub Ventures

Batch of 2010Information Technology

Amit is a serial entrepreneur who has founded three successful startups. His current venture, StartupHub, has helped launch over 200 startups across India.

Key Achievements:

  • Top 30 Under 30 - Business Today (2018)
  • Best Startup Mentor Award (2021)
  • Raised $50M in venture funding

The entrepreneurial spirit I developed during my time at JGEC gave me the courage to take risks and innovate.

Sunita Devi

Vice President

Sunita Devi

Vice President, Global Tech Solutions

Batch of 1998Mechanical Engineering

Sunita broke barriers in the male-dominated manufacturing industry to become one of the youngest VPs at Global Tech Solutions.

Key Achievements:

  • Women in Manufacturing Award (2017)
  • Industry Excellence Award - FICCI (2019)
  • Mentored 100+ women engineers

JGEC gave me the confidence to compete in a challenging industry. The college shaped my character and determination.

Dr. Vikram Singh

Chief Medical Officer

Dr. Vikram Singh

Chief Medical Officer, MedTech Innovations

Batch of 2000Electronics Engineering

Dr. Vikram transitioned from electronics to healthcare technology, revolutionizing medical devices in India.

Key Achievements:

  • Healthcare Innovation Award (2020)
  • Patent holder - Medical devices
  • TED Speaker on HealthTech

The multidisciplinary approach at JGEC helped me see connections between engineering and healthcare that others missed.

Ananya Roy

Senior Director

Ananya Roy

Senior Director, Amazon Web Services

Batch of 2008Computer Science

Ananya leads cloud infrastructure teams at AWS, managing products used by millions of customers worldwide.

Key Achievements:

  • AWS Leadership Award (2022)
  • Women in Cloud Computing (2021)
  • Speaker at re:Invent 2023

The problem-solving skills I learned at JGEC are something I use every day at one of the world's biggest tech companies.
